#. type: Title #
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "A module is an application part grouped around a business context or a reusable feature. In Yii, this is a design boundary, not a required base class. A module can be:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "application code under the `App\\` namespace;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "a [Composer package](package.md) installed into `vendor/`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "code that starts in the application and is later extracted into a package."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "Use a module when a group of actions, domain services, repositories, event handlers, views, assets, commands, and related configuration changes together and has a name that makes sense to the business."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "For example, a blog module can live in an application as:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"src/\n"
"    Blog/\n"
"        Post/\n"
"            Post.php\n"
"            PostRepositoryInterface.php\n"
"            InMemoryPostRepository.php\n"
"        Web/\n"
"            IndexAction.php\n"
"            index.php\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "The same structure can later become a Composer package by changing the namespace and adding package metadata and configuration files. See [Designing packages](designing-packages.md) for package-specific details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Module boundaries"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "Keep module code together by context first and by technical type second. This is close to the [vertical slices](../../cookbook/organizing-code/structuring-by-use-case-with-vertical-slices.md) approach, but at a larger application-structure boundary. Prefer `App\\Blog\\Post\\PostRepositoryInterface` over a global `App\\Repository\\PostRepositoryInterface` when the repository belongs to blog posts only."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "Treat module classes as a public API only when another module is expected to use them. Good public API classes are usually:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "commands or queries that express a use case;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "DTOs or value objects passed between modules;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "interfaces for services another module may call;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "events emitted by the module."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "Keep implementation classes private to the module namespace. Other modules should not depend on `App\\Blog\\Post\\InMemoryPostRepository` or a controller action directly. They should depend on an interface, a use case class, or an event."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Interfaces between modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "Put an interface where the contract belongs:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "If the interface describes a capability provided by a module, place it in that module. For example, `App\\Blog\\Post\\PostRepositoryInterface` belongs to the blog module because it describes how blog posts are read."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "If the interface describes what a module needs from the outside world, place it in the consuming module. For example, `App\\Order\\Customer\\CustomerVerifierInterface` belongs to the order module if orders only need a yes-or-no customer check. The customer module, an application adapter, or a package can provide the implementation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "This keeps dependencies explicit. A module can depend on another module's public contract, but it should not reach into another module's internal implementation classes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "First, define the interface in the module:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<?php\n"
"\n"
"declare(strict_types=1);\n"
"\n"
"namespace App\\Blog\\Post;\n"
"\n"
"interface PostRepositoryInterface\n"
"{\n"
"    /**\n"
"     * @return list<Post>\n"
"     */\n"
"    public function findLatest(): array;\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "Put the implementation in the same module and bind the interface to it:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<?php\n"
"\n"
"declare(strict_types=1);\n"
"\n"
"use App\\Blog\\Post\\InMemoryPostRepository;\n"
"use App\\Blog\\Post\\PostRepositoryInterface;\n"
"\n"
"return [\n"
"    PostRepositoryInterface::class => InMemoryPostRepository::class,\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "In the default application template, put this file under `config/common/di/`, for example `config/common/di/blog.php`. The template loads `config/common/di/*.php` into the shared `di` configuration group, so the binding is available to web and console entry points."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Actions"
msgid "Web actions"
msgstr "Действия"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "Actions belong to the module when they are the web entry point for module behavior:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "final class MyService implements MyServiceInterface\n"
#| "{\n"
#| "    public function __construct(int $amount)\n"
#| "    {\n"
#| "    }\n"
#| "\n"
#| "    public function setDiscount(int $discount): void\n"
#| "    {\n"
#| "    \n"
#| "    }\n"
#| "}\n"
msgid ""
"<?php\n"
"\n"
"declare(strict_types=1);\n"
"\n"
"namespace App\\Blog\\Web;\n"
"\n"
"use App\\Blog\\Post\\PostRepositoryInterface;\n"
"use Psr\\Http\\Message\\ResponseInterface;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Yii\\View\\Renderer\\WebViewRenderer;\n"
"\n"
"final readonly class IndexAction\n"
"{\n"
"    public function __construct(\n"
"        private PostRepositoryInterface $posts,\n"
"        private WebViewRenderer $viewRenderer,\n"
"    ) {\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    public function __invoke(): ResponseInterface\n"
"    {\n"
"        return $this->viewRenderer->render(__DIR__ . '/index', [\n"
"            'posts' => $this->posts->findLatest(),\n"
"        ]);\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"class MyService implements MyServiceInterface\n"
"{\n"
"    public function __construct(int $amount)\n"
"    {\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    public function setDiscount(int $discount): void\n"
"    {\n"
"    \n"
"    }\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "Keep request parsing and response creation in the action. Keep business decisions in the module's domain classes or use case services."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Now, to map your handler to URL, you need to add a route in `config/common/routes.php`:"
msgid "For a small application, add module routes directly to `config/common/routes.php`:"
msgstr "Теперь, чтобы связать ваш обработчик с URL, добавьте маршрут в `config/common/routes.php`:"

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<?php\n"
"\n"
"declare(strict_types=1);\n"
"\n"
"use App\\Blog\\Web\\IndexAction;\n"
"use App\\Web;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Router\\Group;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Router\\Route;\n"
"\n"
"return [\n"
"    Group::create()\n"
"        ->routes(\n"
"            Route::get('/')\n"
"                ->action(Web\\HomePage\\Action::class)\n"
"                ->name('home'),\n"
"        ),\n"
"\n"
"    Group::create('/blog')\n"
"        ->routes(\n"
"            Route::get('')\n"
"                ->action(IndexAction::class)\n"
"                ->name('blog/index'),\n"
"        ),\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "Use module-prefixed route names, such as `blog/index`, to avoid collisions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
msgid "If the application has many modules, you can give each module its own route config file. Change the `routes` group in `config/configuration.php`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"'routes' => [\n"
"    'common/routes.php',\n"
"    'common/routes/*.php',\n"
"],\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Adjust `config/common/routes.php`:"
msgid "Then create `config/common/routes/blog.php`:"
msgstr "Измените файл `config/common/routes.php`:"

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/structure/module.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<?php\n"
"\n"
"declare(strict_types=1);\n"
"\n"
"use App\\Blog\\Web\\IndexAction;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Router\\Group;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Router\\Route;\n"
"\n"
"return [\n"
"    Group::create('/blog')\n"
"        ->routes(\n"
"            Route::get('')\n"
"                ->action(IndexAction::class)\n"
"                ->name('blog/index'),\n"
"        ),\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

